  "name": "Skinstitch Salve",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>This sticky salve stubbornly holds wounds closed and encourages swift natural healing. You can activate the salve in either of the following ways.</p>\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">1</span> Interact</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.MHLuKy4nQO2Z4Am1]{Administer First Aid} without requiring @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.s1vB3HdXjMigYAnY]{Healer's Tools}. You either gain a +2 item bonus to the Medicine check, or you can use the skinstitch salve's Medicine modifier of [[/r 1d20+13]] instead of your own.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">F</span> Interact</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> You @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.1kGNdIIhuglAjIp9]{Treat Wounds} or use @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.Item.wYerMk6F1RZb0Fwt]{Battle Medicine}</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You gain a +2 item bonus to the triggering Medicine check. If you roll a success on the Medicine check, you get a critical success instead.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-effects.Item.zlSNbMDIlTOpcO8R]{Effect: Skinstitch Salve}</p>"
    },
